    Compute the manifold of gene expressions

    compute_manifold.Rd

    Compute the manifold of gene expressions

    compute_manifold(
  counts,
  method = "SAVER",
  preprocess = TRUE,
  ncores = 1,
  nfeatures = 3000,
  dims = 20,
  neighbors = 20
)

    Arguments

    counts

    An expression count matrix. The rows correspond to genes and the columns correspond to cells. It can be sparse.

    method

    Method for estimating the manifold. Can be either "SAVER", which uses SAVER to recover the true expression, or 'neighbor', which uses nearest neighbors to approximate the true expression

    preprocess

    Whether the expression count matrix should be preprocessed, where all genes with zero counts will removed. Default is TRUE.

    ncores

    Number of cores to use. Default is 1. (SAVER only)

    nfeatures

    Number of features to use for FindVariableFeatures. Default is 3000. (Neighbor-based only)

    dims

    Number of dimensions for nearest neighbors. Default is 20.(Neighbor-based only)

    neighbors

    Number of neighbors to output. Default is 20. (Neighbor-based only)

    Value

    A matrix of estimated gene expressions.

'hematopoietic precursor cell', 'megakaryocyte-erythroid progenitor cell',
'precursor B cell'))
